#. <section class="sutta" id="an7.50"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.50:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.50:0.2"
msgid "5. Mahāyaññavagga"
msgstr "5. A Great Sacrifice"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an7.50:0.3"
msgid "50. Methunasutta"
msgstr "50. Sex"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.54"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an7.50:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings "
"with him."

msgctxt "an7.50:1.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an7.50:1.3"
msgid "“bhavampi no gotamo brahmacārī paṭijānātī”ti?"
msgstr "“Does Master Gotama claim to be celibate?”"

msgctxt "an7.50:1.4"
msgid "“Yañhi taṃ, brāhmaṇa, sammā vadamāno vadeyya:"
msgstr "“Brahmin, if anyone should be rightly said to"

msgctxt "an7.50:1.5"
msgid ""
"‘akhaṇḍaṃ acchiddaṃ asabalaṃ akammāsaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ "
"caratī’ti, mameva taṃ, brāhmaṇa, sammā vadamāno vadeyya:"
msgstr ""
"live the celibate life unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, full "
"and pure, it’s me.”"

msgctxt "an7.50:1.6"
msgid ""
"‘ahañhi, brāhmaṇa, akhaṇḍaṃ acchiddaṃ asabalaṃ akammāsaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ "
"parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.50:1.7"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, brahmacariyassa khaṇḍampi chiddampi sabalampi "
"kammāsampī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But what, Master Gotama, is there a break, taint, stain, or mar in "
"celibacy?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an7.50:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā sammā brahmacārī paṭijānamāno "
"na heva kho mātugāmena saddhiṃ dvayaṃdvayasamāpattiṃ samāpajjati;"
msgstr ""
"“Firstly, an ascetic or brahmin who claims to be perfectly celibate does not "
"mutually engage in sex with a female."

msgctxt "an7.50:2.2"
msgid "api ca kho mātugāmassa ucchādanaparimaddananhāpanasambāhanaṃ sādiyati."
msgstr ""
"However, they consent to being anointed, massaged, bathed, and rubbed by a "
"female."

#. VAR: taṃ assādeti → so tadassādeti (bj)
msgctxt "an7.50:2.3"
msgid "So taṃ assādeti, taṃ nikāmeti, tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati."
msgstr "They enjoy it and like it and find it satisfying."

msgctxt "an7.50:2.4"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, brāhmaṇa, brahmacariyassa khaṇḍampi chiddampi sabalampi "
"kammāsampi."
msgstr "This is a break, taint, stain, or mar in celibacy."

#. VAR: jarāya maraṇena → jarāmaraṇena (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.50:2.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, aparisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carati, saṃyutto "
"methunena saṃyogena na parimuccati jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi "
"dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, na parimuccati dukkhasmāti vadāmi. (1)"
msgstr ""
"This is called one who lives the celibate life impurely, tied to the fetter "
"of sex. They’re not freed from rebirth, old age, death, sorrow, lamentation, "
"pain, sadness, and distress. They’re not freed from suffering, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.55"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an7.50:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, idhekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā sammā brahmacārī "
"paṭijānamāno na heva kho mātugāmena saddhiṃ dvayaṃdvayasamāpattiṃ "
"samāpajjati, napi mātugāmassa ucchādanaparimaddananhāpanasambāhanaṃ sādiyati;"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, an ascetic of brahmin who claims to be perfectly celibate does "
"not mutually engage in sex with a female. Nor do they consent to massage and "
"bathing."

msgctxt "an7.50:3.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho mātugāmena saddhiṃ sañjagghati saṅkīḷati saṅkelāyati … pe …. (2)"
msgstr "However, they giggle and play and have fun with females. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an7.50:4.1"
msgid "Napi mātugāmena saddhiṃ sañjagghati saṅkīḷati saṅkelāyati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.50:4.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho mātugāmassa cakkhunā cakkhuṃ upanijjhāyati pekkhati … pe …. (3)"
msgstr "they gaze into a female’s eyes. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an7.50:5.1"
msgid "Napi mātugāmassa cakkhunā cakkhuṃ upanijjhāyati pekkhati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.50:5.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho mātugāmassa saddaṃ suṇāti tirokuṭṭaṃ vā tiropākāraṃ vā hasantiyā "
"vā bhaṇantiyā vā gāyantiyā vā rodantiyā vā … pe …. (4)"
msgstr ""
"they listen through a wall or rampart to the sound of females laughing or "
"chatting or singing or crying. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an7.50:6.1"
msgid ""
"Napi mātugāmassa saddaṃ suṇāti tirokuṭṭaṃ vā tiropākāraṃ vā hasantiyā vā "
"bhaṇantiyā vā gāyantiyā vā rodantiyā vā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.50:6.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho yānissa tāni pubbe mātugāmena saddhiṃ hasitalapitakīḷitāni tāni "
"anussarati … pe …. (5)"
msgstr "they recall when they used to laugh, chat, and have fun with females …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an7.50:7.1"
msgid ""
"Napi yānissa tāni pubbe mātugāmena saddhiṃ hasitalapitakīḷitāni tāni "
"anussarati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.50:7.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho passati gahapatiṃ vā gahapatiputtaṃ vā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi "
"samappitaṃ samaṅgībhūtaṃ paricārayamānaṃ … pe …. (6)"
msgstr ""
"they see a householder or their child amusing themselves, supplied and "
"provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.56"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an7.50:8.1"
msgid ""
"Napi passati gahapatiṃ vā gahapatiputtaṃ vā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitaṃ "
"samaṅgībhūtaṃ paricārayamānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They don’t see a householder or their child amusing themselves, supplied and "
"provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "an7.50:8.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ paṇidhāya brahmacariyaṃ carati imināhaṃ "
"sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā devo vā bhavissāmi "
"devaññataro vāti."
msgstr ""
"However, they live the celibate life wishing to be reborn in one of the "
"orders of gods. They think: ‘By this precept or observance or mortification "
"or spiritual life, may I become one of the gods!’"

msgctxt "an7.50:8.3"
msgid "So taṃ assādeti, taṃ nikāmeti, tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati."
msgstr "They enjoy it and like it and find it satisfying."

msgctxt "an7.50:8.4"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, brāhmaṇa, brahmacariyassa khaṇḍampi chiddampi sabalampi "
"kammāsampi."
msgstr "This is a break, taint, stain, or mar in celibacy."

msgctxt "an7.50:8.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, aparisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carati saṃyutto methunena "
"saṃyogena, na parimuccati jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi "
"domanassehi upāyāsehi, na parimuccati dukkhasmāti vadāmi. (7)"
msgstr ""
"This is called one who lives the celibate life impurely, tied to the fetter "
"of sex. They’re not free from rebirth, old age, death, sorrow, lamentation, "
"pain, sadness, and distress. They’re not free from suffering, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
#. VAR: aññataraññataramethunasaṃyogaṃ → aññataraññataraṃ methunasaṃyogaṃ (bj, pts1) | aññataraṃ methunasaṃyogaṃ (si) | aññtaraṃ methunasaññogaṃ (s1-3)
#. VAR: abhisambuddhoti paccaññāsiṃ → abhisambuddho paccaññāsiṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.50:9.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imesaṃ sattannaṃ methunasaṃyogānaṃ "
"aññataraññataramethunasaṃyogaṃ attani appahīnaṃ samanupassiṃ, neva tāvāhaṃ, "
"brāhmaṇa, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya "
"sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paccaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"As long as I saw that these seven sexual fetters—or even one of them—had not "
"been given up in me, I didn’t announce my supreme perfect awakening in this "
"world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics "
"and brahmins, its gods and humans."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an7.50:10.1"
msgid ""
"Yato ca khohaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imesaṃ sattannaṃ methunasaṃyogānaṃ "
"aññataraññataramethunasaṃyogaṃ attani appahīnaṃ na samanupassiṃ, athāhaṃ, "
"brāhmaṇa, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya "
"sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paccaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"But when I saw that these seven sexual fetters—every one of them—had been "
"given up in me, I announced my supreme perfect awakening in this world with "
"its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and "
"brahmins, its gods and humans."

msgctxt "an7.50:10.2"
msgid "‘Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi,"
msgstr "Knowledge and vision arose in me:"

#. VAR: vimutti → cetovimutti (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an7.50:10.3"
msgid "akuppā me vimutti, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘My freedom is unshakable; this is my last rebirth; now there are no more "
"future lives.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an7.50:11.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an7.50:11.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …"
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! …"

msgctxt "an7.50:11.3"
msgid ""
"upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.50:11.4"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
